FBI have recovered a 26-pound gold bar from the robbery in South Florida found in North Carolina last month . 
  The gold bars were stolen in a $5 million armored truck robbery from Miami to Boston on March 1 . 
  Truck pulled over when one of the guards 'felt sick' on the way to Boston . 
  Three armed men 'ordered guards to lie on the ground and took 275lbs of gold' Police suspect it was an inside job because of suspicious stop . 
  The FBI say they recovered the gold bar - believed to be worth up to $500,000 - from South Florida . 
  The heist occurred on Interstate 95 in Wilson County . 
 